27 (26). Fronto-orbital area lacking enlarged setulae. Ocellar plate greatly expanded, with posterior ocelli widely spread, much farther apart than distance between anterior and one posterior ocellus. Ocellar seta present in females, but usually absent in males that instead have ocellar plate densely pilose and fuzzy. Nearctic, Neotropical......................... (
Leucopina Malloch
